---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="CV | Vincenzo Di Perna"
  description="CV of Vincenzo Di Perna, Blockchain Systems & Digital Assets Engineer."
  sideBarActiveItemID="cv"
>
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">CV</h1>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-90">
      I am a Blockchain Systems & Digital Assets Engineer with a PhD in Blockchain & DLT,
      focused on distributed systems, blockchain benchmarking, reproducible experimentation,
      protocol evaluation, data analysis, and digital-asset infrastructures.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/cv/Di_Perna_CV.pdf" target="_blank">
        Download CV
      </a>

      <a class="btn btn-outline" href="https://github.com/vindipe" target="_blank">
        GitHub
      </a>

      <a class="btn btn-outline" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/vincenzo-di-perna/" target="_blank">
        LinkedIn
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Profile</h2>

    <div class="text-justify leading-relaxed">
      <p class="mb-4">
        My work combines distributed systems research, experimental methodology,
        blockchain infrastructure evaluation, and data-driven analysis. During my PhD,
        I designed and used reproducible benchmarking pipelines to study how blockchain
        systems behave under different workloads, network topologies, and operational
        conditions.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4">
        I am particularly interested in performance and latency evaluation, energy
        efficiency, repeatability, performance predictability, protocol analytics,
        digital-asset and CBDC-related infrastructures, and research engineering practices that
        make experimental results easier to reproduce and compare.
      </p>

      <p>
        I am open to engineering, R&D, data, research, and hybrid roles where rigorous
        experimentation, distributed systems knowledge, and blockchain/digital-asset
        expertise can support practical technical decisions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Education</h2>

    <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4">
      <TimeLineElement
        title="PhD in Blockchain & Distributed Ledger Technology"
        subtitle="Università di Camerino, Italy"
        date="2022–2025"
      >
        Dissertation focused on comparing blockchain systems across performance,
        energy, repeatability, predictability, and economic-efficiency dimensions.
        Research included topology-aware benchmarking, reproducible experimentation,
        workload design, network emulation, and statistical analysis of blockchain
        system behavior.
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="MSc in ICT Solutions Architect"
        subtitle="Università di Pisa, Italy"
        date="2019–2022"
      >
        Graduate studies focused on ICT architectures, software systems, networks,
        security, and technical design of digital infrastructures.
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="BSc in Computer Systems and Network Security"
        subtitle="Università degli Studi di Milano, Italy"
        date="2015–2019"
      >
        Foundation in computer systems, operating systems, networks, cybersecurity,
        programming, and technical problem solving.
      </TimeLineElement>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Certifications</h2>

    <div class="grid gap-4">
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between gap-2">
            <h3 class="card-title">
              Blockchain for Business Certificate
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-outline shrink-0">2023</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            SUPSI / USI / Franklin University Switzerland / City of Lugano.
          </p>

          <p class="opacity-80">
            Professional certificate focused on blockchain applications, business
            use cases, and digital-asset-related innovation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section> 

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Research & Engineering Experience</h2>

    <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4">
      <TimeLineElement
        title="Blockchain Benchmarking & Distributed Systems Research"
        subtitle="PhD research and related research"
        date="2022-"
      >
        Designed, executed, and analyzed reproducible blockchain experiments across
        multiple platforms, workloads, and network conditions. Evaluated throughput,
        latency, energy usage, variability, repeatability, and performance predictability
        under controlled experimental settings.
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="Lilith — Topology-Aware Blockchain Benchmarking Framework"
        subtitle="Research artifact and experimental toolchain"
        date="2022-"
      >
        Built a benchmarking framework integrating blockchain workload generation,
        network emulation, orchestration, and data analysis. Used it to study how
        topology and workload interactions affect blockchain performance and energy
        behavior.
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="Digital Assets & CBDC-Oriented Data Workflows"
        subtitle="Protocol analytics, dashboards, and structured data analysis"
        date="2022-"
      >
        Worked on data-oriented analysis and dashboard concepts for digital assets,
        digital-asset and CBDC-related infrastructures, and blockchain ecosystem indicators,
        connecting technical protocol behavior with analytical and economic perspectives.
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="Research Engineering & Reproducibility"
        subtitle="Software artifacts, datasets, pipelines, and experimental methodology"
        date="2022-"
      >
        Developed scripts, datasets, reproducible workflows, statistical analyses,
        and documentation to support repeatable experiments and transparent evaluation
        of blockchain systems.
      </TimeLineElement>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Selected Publications</h2>

    <div class="grid gap-4">
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between gap-2">
            <h3 class="card-title">
              Impact of Network Topologies on Blockchain Performance
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary shrink-0">ACM DEBS'25</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Vincenzo P. Di Perna, Marco Bernardo, Francesco Fabris,
            Sebastião Amaro, Miguel Matos, and Valerio Schiavoni.
          </p>

          <p class="opacity-80">
            Proceedings of the 19th ACM International Conference on Distributed
            and Event-Based Systems, 2025.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3701717.3730540"
              target="_blank"
            >
              DOI / Paper
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between gap-2">
            <h3 class="card-title">
              Blockchain Energy Consumption: Unveiling the Impact of Network Topologies
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary shrink-0">IEEE ICBC'25</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Vincenzo P. Di Perna, Valerio Schiavoni, Francesco Fabris,
            and Marco Bernardo.
          </p>

          <p class="opacity-80">
            Proceedings of the 2025 IEEE International Conference on Blockchain
            and Cryptocurrency.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/11114569"
              target="_blank"
            >
              IEEE Xplore
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between gap-2">
            <h3 class="card-title">
              An Entropy-Based Approach to Evaluating the Economic Efficiency of Cryptocurrencies
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-secondary shrink-0">DLT'25</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Vincenzo P. Di Perna, Michele Foderaro, Francesco Fabris,
            and Marco Bernardo.
          </p>

          <p class="opacity-80">
            Distributed Ledger Technology Workshop, CEUR Workshop Proceedings,
            Vol. 4105, 2025.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://ceur-ws.org/Vol-4105/paper09.pdf"
              target="_blank"
            >
              CEUR paper
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between gap-2">
            <h3 class="card-title">
              Dynamic Taxonomy: a Bridge from DeFi to TradFi
            </h3>
            <span class="badge badge-outline shrink-0">SSRN</span>
          </div>

          <p>
            Working paper on digital assets, decentralized finance, traditional
            finance, and taxonomy-oriented analysis.
          </p>

          <p class="opacity-80">
            SSRN working paper.
          </p>

          <div class="card-actions justify-end">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=5034378"
              target="_blank"
            >
              SSRN
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Projects & Artifacts</h2>

    <div class="grid gap-4">
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Lilith</h3>
          <p>
            Topology-aware blockchain benchmarking framework integrating workload
            generation, network emulation, orchestration, and experiment analysis.
          </p>
          <div class="card-actions justify-end">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.11409100"
              target="_blank"
            >
              Zenodo artifact
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Blockchain Repeatability Dataset</h3>
          <p>
            Dataset and repeated experimental campaign for studying blockchain
            performance variability, repeatability, and predictability.
          </p>
          <div class="card-actions justify-end">
            <a
              class="btn btn-sm btn-outline"
              href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15545963"
              target="_blank"
            >
              Zenodo dataset
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
</div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Technical Skills</h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Programming & scripting</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc mx-6 grid gap-1">
            <li>Python</li>
            <li>Bash</li>
            <li>Rust familiarity</li>
            <li>JavaScript / TypeScript basics</li>
            <li>Git and GitHub workflows</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Systems & infrastructure</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc mx-6 grid gap-1">
            <li>Linux</li>
            <li>Docker</li>
            <li>Network emulation</li>
            <li>Distributed systems experimentation</li>
            <li>Benchmark orchestration</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Blockchain & digital assets</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc mx-6 grid gap-1">
            <li>Blockchain benchmarking</li>
            <li>Protocol evaluation</li>
            <li>Digital-asset analytics</li>
            <li>CBDC-related research context</li>
            <li>Performance, latency, and energy analysis</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title">Data & experimentation</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc mx-6 grid gap-1">
            <li>Reproducible experiments</li>
            <li>Experimental design</li>
            <li>Statistical analysis</li>
            <li>Data pipelines</li>
            <li>Dashboard-style visual analytics</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>